---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

// Person structured data — /about is the canonical identity page for the site.
const person = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Trent Jones',
  url: 'https://rtrentjones.dev/about/',
  jobTitle: 'Senior Software Development Engineer',
  worksFor: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Amazon' },
  alumniOf: { '@type': 'CollegeOrUniversity', name: 'University of Southern California' },
  sameAs: ['https://github.com/RTrentJones', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/rtrentjones'],
};
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Trent Jones — senior engineer across product and platform: full-stack products, the developer tooling that makes teams faster, and genomics software."
  prose
  structuredData={person}
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p class="positioning">
    I build user-facing products end to end, and the platforms and tooling that make building them
    faster — systems that make experts better at their work.
  </p>

  <h2>What I do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Full-stack product</strong> — user-facing apps end to end, from schema and auth to the
      UI.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Developer platforms &amp; release tooling</strong> — paved-path systems other teams
      adopt because they make them faster: release pipelines, internal CLIs, agent tooling.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Scientific &amp; clinical software</strong> — genomics tooling built around expert
      judgment, under clinical-grade correctness bars.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>AI-native tooling</strong> — agents and MCP servers with real verification (evals,
      protocol checks), so a model augments an expert instead of guessing.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Experience</h2>
  <p>
    I'm a senior full-stack engineer with 11 years in the industry, the last 7 at
    Amazon, where I've worked on Alexa across both the mobile and web surfaces.
    My teams deliver product first, but the
    work I reach for is the pipelines and tooling that make that delivery go faster for the people
    around me. For three-plus years I owned the release pipeline that more than twenty teams across
    two orgs shipped through, and I built Vertex, an internal agent-tooling system that's been
    adopted across the org.
  </p>
  <p>
    Before Amazon I was the second engineer at
    <a href="https://www.fulgentgenetics.com/">Fulgent Genetics</a>, a clinical genetics lab, where
    I built the variant-curation platform clinical scientists used to call variants — along with the
    LIMS (lab information management software) and the FulgentGenetics.com ordering portal.
  </p>
  <p>
    I studied at <strong>USC</strong>, where I earned dual degrees in <strong>neuroscience</strong>
    and <strong>computer science</strong>. The biology didn't stay in the background — I'm drawn to
    the seam between software and the life sciences, and some of what I build lives there (see
    <a href="/bamcp/">BAMCP</a>, which puts genomic evidence in front of an AI agent).
  </p>

  <h2>Selected proof points</h2>
  <p>
    A thread I keep pulling on is making verification automatic — so everything here ships and
    re-verifies through my own <a href="https://github.com/RTrentJones/greenlight">Greenlight</a>
    loop, and this site runs on it too.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/greenlight/">Greenlight</a> — a deploy → verify → promote framework spanning
      Cloudflare, Vercel, Oracle Cloud, and Neon.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/pg_kafka/">pg_kafka</a> — a PostgreSQL extension that speaks the Kafka wire protocol,
      backed by conformance and benchmark evidence.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/bamcp/">BAMCP</a> — an MCP server that puts genomic alignment evidence in front of an
      AI agent.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/heistmind/">HeistMind</a> — an authenticated full-stack app, verified against the
      live deploy.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Reach me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/rtrentjones">LinkedIn</a> — best for a first
    message — or find my work on <a href="https://github.com/RTrentJones">GitHub</a>.
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .positioning {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }
</style>
